INSERT INTO public.product_translations (product_id, language, content)
VALUES ('cc0d78d4-5861-417c-bbe0-72fb6805fcb2', 'en', '## Overview

This access control device provides secure personnel management for controlled entry and exit points. Combining multiple authentication methods with real-time event logging, it delivers comprehensive access control for commercial, industrial, and residential environments.

Serves the security and access control market with specialized hardware.

The HIP Car Park Barrier model CMW8133-DC is designed to deliver dependable performance for applications requiring physical access control and entry management capabilities. HIP Car Park Barrier model CMW8133-DC Intelligent Barrier, length 4 meters, when the car barrier is raised The signal light will be green. Powered by a brushless DC motor, motor life up to 5,000,000 times or more. This product is backed by comprehensive documentation and technical support.

## Features

- Multi-factor authentication with card, PIN, fingerprint, and facial recognition
- Anti-passback and anti-tailgating security logic
- Real-time event logging with cloud synchronization
- Integration with third-party access control software
- Tamper detection with automatic alarm triggering
- Support for IC, ID, NFC, and mobile credentials

The HIP Car Park Barrier model CMW8133-DC supports integration with standard management platforms used in physical access control and entry management deployments.

## Applications

The HIP Car Park Barrier model CMW8133-DC is suitable for:

- Commercial office building entrance access control
- Industrial facility restricted area management
- Residential community gate and parking automation
- Educational campus building access and attendance
- Healthcare facility restricted ward management
- Government multi-level security zone enforcement

The device is appropriate for organizations seeking reliable physical access control and entry management solutions.

## Installation Notes

**Important:** Review all documentation before installation.

1. Mount at door handle height 1.2 to 1.5 meters
2. Run shielded network and power cabling
3. Connect to controller or network switch
4. Initialize through management software
5. Enroll credentials and configure access groups.
6. Test all entry and exit scenarios
